name: alpha,alpha-trehalase
classes: Glycosidases, i.e. enzymes that hydrolyse O- and S-glycosyl compounds
comment: The enzyme is an anomer-inverting glucosidase that catalyses the hydrolysis of the alpha-glucosidic O-linkage of alpha,alpha-trehalose, releasing initially equimolar amounts of alpha- and beta-D-glucose. It is widely distributed in microorganisms, plants, invertebrates and vertebrates.
